xfce on docker
==============

Connecting over network with xrdp

it is split up in xrdp1 and xrdp2
because the build process is much shorter 
if there are changes to do.

higher than xrdp2 is optional,
it just installs more optional software.

#run
docker run -v ~/docker/volume/myHome:/home/abc/Documents \
           -v ~/docker/volume/ssh_etc:/etc/ssh  --rm -it --name \
           con_xrdp --hostname xrdp_server --shm-size 1g xrdp2


#####
connect to the machine with:
rdesktop -rsound -g 1400x860  172.17.0.2


###################
## Ada Arm Gps
docker run -v ~/docker/volume/myHome/ada_arm:/home/abc/Documents \
           -v ~/docker/volume/ssh_etc:/etc/ssh  \
           --privileged \
           -v /dev/bus/usb:/dev/bus/usb  \
           --rm -it --name con_xrdp \
           --hostname xrdp_server \
           --shm-size 1g \
           xrdp_adagpsarm
           

-------------------
Known problems:
Desktop icon can not be generated automatically.
It has to be manually  copied:
cp /tmp/gps_arm.desktop /home/abc/Desktop/gps_arm.desktop
   
   
   
###################
## Ada Gps
docker run -v ~/docker/volume/myHome/ada_gtk:/home/abc/Documents \
           -v ~/docker/volume/ssh_etc:/etc/ssh  \
           --rm -it --name con_xrdp \
           --hostname xrdp_server \
           --shm-size 1g \
           xrdp_adagps
           
-------------------
Known problems:
Desktop icon can not be generated automatically.
It has to be manually  copied:
cp /tmp/gps.desktop /home/abc/Desktop/gps.desktop

###################
## Android
docker run -v ~/docker/volume/myHome/android:/home/abc/Documents \
           -v ~/docker/volume/ssh_etc:/etc/ssh  \
           --privileged \
           -v /dev/bus/usb:/dev/bus/usb  \
           --rm -it --name con_xrdp \
           --hostname xrdp_server \
           --shm-size 1g \
           android
           
-------------------
Known problems:
Desktop icon can not be generated automatically.
It has to be manually  copied:
cp /tmp/Android.desktop /home/abc/Desktop/Android.desktop           

